classificationSchemaList.csDefinition: Version 2.8 The Cancer Central Clinical Participent Registry (C3PR) is a web-based application used to manage participants in cancer clinical trials. Research staff will use C3PR as a participant-centric entry point to clinical trial management systems. C3PR provides a central registry for study participants, and it enables the end-user to access participant-centric information that is stored in multiple clinical trial systems. Participants that can be tracked include patients or potential patients, their guardians, family members, and referring physicians. The system also allows tracking other types of participants such as principal investigators, caregivers, referring physicians, and the users of the system.
